                    <comment id="12919557" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Sun, 10 Oct 2010 04:05:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch.  The query value was changed to BufferedDeletes.Num instead of Integer to save a little on object pointer allocation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a side note, there are a number of unrelated generics warnings when compiling.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12926250" author="rcmuir" created="Fri, 29 Oct 2010 13:48:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;moving out&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12985269" author="shaie" created="Sun, 23 Jan 2011 07:48:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jason, are you going to fix it for 3.1, or shall I mark it 3.2?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12985406" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Sun, 23 Jan 2011 20:45:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you mean post a patch for 3.1?  The change is fairly simple, can you simply add it and commit?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12985511" author="shaie" created="Mon, 24 Jan 2011 04:28:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah I can add it. I didn&apos;t realize you&apos;re waiting for someone to take on that issue &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;20&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12985512" author="shaie" created="Mon, 24 Jan 2011 04:34:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I reviewed the patch and it no longer applies to DocumentsWriter anymore, since deletes happen inside SegmentDeletes. So:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;delete-by-term: am I right to say it&apos;s handled properly in SegmentDeletes.addTerm()?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;delete-by-query: seems like SegmentDeletes.addQuery() always increments bytesUsed, whether the query was already in the map or not. I think that&apos;s wrong, so I&apos;ll add a patch that fixes it for you to review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12985516" author="shaie" created="Mon, 24 Jan 2011 04:47:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch against 3x, though I believe it&apos;ll look the same against trunk. Fixed SegmentDeletes.addQuery and added a CHANGES entry. I&apos;d appreciate if someone can take a look before I commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12985694" author="mikemccand" created="Mon, 24 Jan 2011 14:07:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch looks good Shai!  We had already fixed the dup-Term case...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12985737" author="shaie" created="Mon, 24 Jan 2011 15:36:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1062824 (3x).&lt;br/&gt;
Committed revision 1062832 (trunk).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Jason !&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
